WEBVTT

00:02.503 --> 00:04.505
Previously on Empire...
When Hakeem wins,

00:04.538 --> 00:06.807
I get to release Jamal's next
album through Lyon Dynasty.

00:06.840 --> 00:07.975
LUCIOUS:
Bet.

00:08.008 --> 00:10.144
Times would like to do
a profile on Jamal.

00:10.178 --> 00:11.579
That's gonna be a little tricky,
isn't it?

00:11.612 --> 00:14.382
Seeing Jamal's got
a girlfriend and all.

00:14.415 --> 00:16.184
NICOLE RICHIE:
This has to be the first time

00:16.217 --> 00:17.185
in the history
of the American Sound Awards

00:17.218 --> 00:18.486
that a father and son

00:18.519 --> 00:19.753
are going toe to toe.

00:19.787 --> 00:21.422
Ain't that a bitch?

00:21.455 --> 00:23.857
Lucious is just obsessed

00:23.891 --> 00:25.593
with this grandchild.

00:25.626 --> 00:27.228
My beautiful wife,

00:27.261 --> 00:28.929
Camilla Marks Whiteman.

00:28.962 --> 00:30.064
Remember me, Lucious?

00:31.299 --> 00:32.933
You have to trust
and believe me.

00:32.966 --> 00:35.236
I can take you
to the next level, Hakeem.

00:35.269 --> 00:36.570
HAKEEM:
Think I'm in love.

00:36.604 --> 00:38.206
I ain't never feel this way
in my life.

00:38.239 --> 00:41.008
I propose a vote
to remove Lucious Lyon

00:41.041 --> 00:43.444
as chairman of Empire.

00:43.477 --> 00:45.279
Hakeem, no!

00:45.313 --> 00:46.080
Aye.

00:47.781 --> 00:49.583
(alarm blaring)
(groans)

00:49.617 --> 00:51.719
What keeps setting
this thing off?

00:51.752 --> 00:52.453
(gasps)

00:56.490 --> 00:58.492
*

01:11.172 --> 01:13.307
(groaning)

01:18.646 --> 01:20.248
(door closes)

01:23.651 --> 01:25.719
Pop.

01:25.753 --> 01:27.054
Please, will you
listen to me?

01:27.087 --> 01:28.556
This is a huge mistake.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.057
We should just...
we should get out of here.

01:30.090 --> 01:31.925
They already
called the police.

01:31.959 --> 01:34.462
This is my damn company.

01:34.495 --> 01:36.597
I built it from nothing!

01:36.630 --> 01:39.667
And I'll be damned if somebody
gonna take me away from it.

01:39.700 --> 01:42.236
Hey, Lucious, I'm down.

01:42.270 --> 01:43.237
Okay?

01:43.271 --> 01:45.105
I mean, I am down.

01:45.139 --> 01:47.007
Feel me on this.

01:47.040 --> 01:48.442
There's no doubt in my mind

01:48.476 --> 01:50.478
that that emergency vote
was unlawful.

01:50.511 --> 01:53.414
We get our hands
on the corporate charter,

01:53.447 --> 01:56.250
I bet you we'll be able
to prove that this whole

01:56.284 --> 01:57.685
Mimi/Camilla shenanigans
was illegal.

01:57.718 --> 01:58.519
Yeah, let's get the charter.

01:58.552 --> 01:59.853
It's in a safe
at our law firm.

01:59.887 --> 02:01.489
Tomorrow morning, after
we get a good night's sleep,

02:01.522 --> 02:02.823
we'll head down there,
we'll look it up.

02:02.856 --> 02:04.792
No, no, no, no.
You get the charter now.

02:04.825 --> 02:06.594
It's the middle of night, Pop;
they're closed.

02:06.627 --> 02:08.329
Excuses are the tools
of the incompetent.

02:08.362 --> 02:10.831
Doesn't help, Thirsty.

02:13.534 --> 02:15.436
Fine.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.137
If I go down there
right now,

02:17.171 --> 02:18.939
will you two please
leave the building

02:18.972 --> 02:20.274
before the cops get here?
Please.

02:20.308 --> 02:22.476
Get the charter,
'cause I ain't going nowhere.

02:22.510 --> 02:24.011
Yes, sir.

02:33.587 --> 02:36.056
(groans quietly)

02:36.089 --> 02:37.558
(weakly):
Help.

02:39.560 --> 02:42.029
(sobbing)

02:44.064 --> 02:45.799
Help.

02:45.833 --> 02:47.335
(sobs)

02:56.577 --> 02:59.247
Hey, Keem.

02:59.280 --> 03:01.249
*

03:10.224 --> 03:13.227
Why?

03:13.261 --> 03:15.529
Why would you do this
to your family?

03:15.563 --> 03:18.666
I didn't do this
to our family.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.368
I did it to him.

03:20.401 --> 03:23.237
Boy...

03:23.271 --> 03:26.607
you gave our business away to...

03:26.640 --> 03:28.876
that half-lesbian bitch.

03:28.909 --> 03:31.879
You just threw away
our legacy!

03:31.912 --> 03:34.081
And for what?

03:34.114 --> 03:36.717
Did she promise to make you CEO?

03:36.750 --> 03:38.586
No, Mom, they didn't even know
I was gonna make that decision

03:38.619 --> 03:39.853
till right before I voted.

03:39.887 --> 03:42.089
We're gonna call
another meeting,

03:42.122 --> 03:43.757
and you're gonna
take your vote back.

03:43.791 --> 03:46.760
No.

03:46.794 --> 03:48.862
From the second we started
Lyon Dynasty,

03:48.896 --> 03:50.731
Dad been trying to kick us off.

03:50.764 --> 03:52.032
He had it coming.

03:52.065 --> 03:56.003
We all got it coming,
sooner or later.

03:57.505 --> 03:59.473
But you getting ready
to have it coming now,

03:59.507 --> 04:02.142
if you don't
take your vote back.

04:02.175 --> 04:05.579
Take your vote back, Hakeem.

04:05.613 --> 04:07.415
No.

04:07.448 --> 04:09.182
Take it back!

04:10.351 --> 04:11.285
Take it back!
(groans)

04:12.320 --> 04:13.754
Take it back!

04:14.655 --> 04:16.089
Take it back!

04:16.123 --> 04:17.425
Take the damn vote back, boy!

04:17.458 --> 04:18.826
Take the vote back, Hakeem!

04:18.859 --> 04:21.194
I will kill your ass!
You hear me?!
(grunting)

04:23.831 --> 04:25.466
Our next ASA nominee

04:25.499 --> 04:28.001
received a whopping
seven nominations today.

04:28.035 --> 04:30.137
Let's hear it for that, right?
(crowd cheering)

04:30.170 --> 04:32.740
Now to end our nominee
midnight bash,

04:32.773 --> 04:36.577
performing his
ASA-nominated song "Heavy,"

04:36.610 --> 04:39.246
Jamal Lyon.

04:39.279 --> 04:40.614
(crowd cheering)

04:45.653 --> 04:47.621
Thank you.

04:49.122 --> 04:51.625
This has been kind of
the craziest day ever.

04:51.659 --> 04:55.496
Uh, I kind of thought I wasn't
gonna make it here with y'all,

04:55.529 --> 04:57.365
but my mom told me
I had to, so...

04:57.398 --> 04:59.099
(laughter)

04:59.132 --> 05:00.934
Y'all think I'm joking,
but she really did say,

05:00.968 --> 05:02.536
"Jamal, get your ass
over there." (laughs)

05:02.570 --> 05:03.537
(laughter)

05:03.571 --> 05:05.373
I know a lot of y'all

05:05.406 --> 05:07.375
have been talking about
how my dad and I

05:07.408 --> 05:09.109
have been nominated
against each other

05:09.142 --> 05:10.811
and, uh, all the craziness

05:10.844 --> 05:12.112
that's going on
with our company.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.214
But I want
to make it clear tonight

05:14.247 --> 05:17.851
that I support my father 1,000%,

05:17.885 --> 05:20.388
always and forever, so...

05:20.421 --> 05:22.155
Dad, this is for you.

05:25.426 --> 05:27.428
*

05:28.496 --> 05:30.464
* All hail the king

05:30.498 --> 05:33.000
* Yeah

05:33.033 --> 05:37.237
* They say heavy is a head
that wears the crown *

05:37.270 --> 05:41.308
* They say heavy is a head that
wears the crown *

05:41.341 --> 05:44.878
* They say heavy is a head
that wears the crown *

05:44.912 --> 05:46.980
(Rhonda sobbing)
* Always used to think

05:47.014 --> 05:49.082
* That that was just
some damn excuse *

05:49.116 --> 05:51.018
* Something that the weak say

05:51.051 --> 05:52.686
* 'Cause they couldn't
hold it down *

05:52.720 --> 05:54.555
(panting)

05:54.588 --> 05:56.023
* But now that I wear it
(sobs): Oh, no.

05:56.056 --> 05:58.158
* I know that to be true

05:58.191 --> 05:59.860
* Oh

05:59.893 --> 06:03.196
* Daddy raised a soldier
whether he knew it or not *

06:03.230 --> 06:05.566
* He supplied the pain

06:05.599 --> 06:07.601
* I put it in the music,
made it hot *

06:07.635 --> 06:10.037
* Strong back
* Strong shoulders *

06:10.070 --> 06:11.905
Oh, God.
* 'Cause I'm holding up a lot

06:11.939 --> 06:14.374
* I'm underneath this bitch
supporting... *

06:14.408 --> 06:16.109
Please.

06:16.143 --> 06:18.879
Save the baby.

06:18.912 --> 06:20.681
I don't care what happens to me.

06:20.714 --> 06:23.016
* I'm the leader, damn it,
I'm the lead... *

06:23.050 --> 06:26.286
I can die a thousand times;
just please, save my baby.

06:26.319 --> 06:28.255
* Feel the real weight
of this crown *

06:28.288 --> 06:30.057
* Not just the crown

06:30.090 --> 06:33.093
* Feeling like
this whole damn kingdom's *

06:33.126 --> 06:34.528
* Sittin' on top of me, yeah

06:34.562 --> 06:36.530
* Sitting on top of me *

06:36.564 --> 06:38.566
* Sit-Sitting on top of me
(grunts loudly)

06:38.599 --> 06:40.968
* Sitting on top of me *
(glass cracks, alarm blaring)

06:41.001 --> 06:43.537
* And I'm-a carry it
on my back until victory *

06:43.571 --> 06:45.038
(alarm blaring)
* Even though this whole

06:45.072 --> 06:48.408
* Damn kingdom's
sitting on top of me. *

06:48.442 --> 06:49.910
(pounding on door)
MAN: Police!

06:49.943 --> 06:52.613
We got to get
rid of these.

06:54.181 --> 06:55.148
(pounding on door continues)

06:55.182 --> 06:56.484
MAN:
Open the door, sir!

06:56.517 --> 06:57.417
Trust me.

06:59.853 --> 07:01.154
Mr. Lyon!

07:01.188 --> 07:02.422
Okay, we are unarmed, okay?

07:02.456 --> 07:04.558
And unless you have
an arrest warrant,

07:04.592 --> 07:06.126
my client is the CEO
of this company,

07:06.159 --> 07:08.295
which means he has every right
to be in the building.

07:08.328 --> 07:09.262
Former CEO.

07:10.998 --> 07:13.100
This is a little pathetic,
don't you think, Lucious?

07:13.133 --> 07:14.802
You think this is
some kind of game?

07:14.835 --> 07:16.336
Get out of my office.

07:17.805 --> 07:20.340
Bitch, you gonna have to
drag me out of here.

07:20.373 --> 07:22.409
OFFICER:
Mr. Lyon,

07:22.442 --> 07:24.478
if you don't leave the building,
we're gonna have to arrest you

07:24.512 --> 07:26.580
for trespassing.
Trespassing?

07:26.614 --> 07:28.348
In my office?!

07:28.381 --> 07:30.784
I built this company!
Lucious!

07:30.818 --> 07:32.252
Uh, Rhonda's in the hospital.

07:32.285 --> 07:33.420
She might not make it.

07:33.453 --> 07:35.222
(heart beating)

07:40.694 --> 07:43.030
WOMAN (over P.A.):
Code blue, Room 237.

07:43.063 --> 07:44.197
Code blue, Room 237.

07:44.231 --> 07:46.133
Look, y'all.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.638
(sniffles)
Whatever happens,

07:50.671 --> 07:52.873
we're gonna have to pull it
together before Dre gets here.

07:52.906 --> 07:54.107
Yeah.

07:54.141 --> 07:55.776
'Cause he's gonna need us, man.

07:55.809 --> 07:56.544
Yeah.

07:56.577 --> 07:58.378
(door opens)

07:58.411 --> 08:00.147
What happened?
Is she okay?

08:02.082 --> 08:04.618
You stay out of here
while we talk to your brother.

08:04.652 --> 08:06.119
Don't nobody want
to see your ass.

08:06.153 --> 08:09.256
Right now. Get out of here.

08:13.894 --> 08:16.797
Who's gonna tell him?

08:16.830 --> 08:17.965
Here he is.

08:17.998 --> 08:20.033
What happened? Is she okay?

08:20.067 --> 08:22.502
Look...

08:22.536 --> 08:23.904
I'm so sorry, son.

08:23.937 --> 08:24.905
What?

08:24.938 --> 08:26.674
There was an accident.

08:26.707 --> 08:28.676
And sometimes things don't
work out the way you want...

08:28.709 --> 08:30.477
Pop, what are you talk... What?
JAMAL: Dad, wait, wait, wait.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.179
Wait. Rhon-Rhonda's good, man.

08:32.212 --> 08:33.480
She's okay? She's okay?
Yeah, yeah. She's fine.

08:33.513 --> 08:34.848
Baby, baby. Baby, baby.

08:34.882 --> 08:37.818
Rhonda's fine, okay?
She's so strong.

08:37.851 --> 08:40.220
(sniffles)
But...

08:40.253 --> 08:41.989
the baby didn't make it.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.757
Andre,

08:43.791 --> 08:47.094
I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry, Dre.

08:47.127 --> 08:49.429
I'm so sorry, but it's okay.
You guys are young.

08:49.462 --> 08:51.999
You can try again.
No, no, no. It's okay.
I don't understand.

08:52.032 --> 08:53.366
I know.
Dre.

08:53.400 --> 08:54.835
I know, baby. I know.

08:54.868 --> 08:56.403
I know, I know,
I know.

08:56.436 --> 08:57.738
It's gonna be okay. Okay...
Where-where is she?

08:57.771 --> 08:59.439
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
You can't go in there like that!

08:59.472 --> 09:01.842
No, just... I just want to
see her. Get your hands off me!

09:01.875 --> 09:03.510
(overlapping shouting)

09:03.543 --> 09:06.780
Dre! Dre!
Get off me! Get off me!

09:06.814 --> 09:08.882
They gonna come
take you away, Dre. Stop.

09:08.916 --> 09:10.117
LUCIOUS: Dre!
ANDRE: Let me go!

09:10.150 --> 09:11.885
Dre!
Let me go! (sobbing)

09:14.554 --> 09:15.923
(sighs)

09:15.956 --> 09:18.592
I just don't get it.

09:18.626 --> 09:21.795
I don't know
what happened.

09:21.829 --> 09:23.530
I must have slipped
or something.

09:23.563 --> 09:26.399
I don't know.
I'm so sorry, Andre.

09:26.433 --> 09:27.901
It's all my fault.

09:27.935 --> 09:29.737
It was an accident.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.939
Don't blame
yourself for this.

09:31.972 --> 09:34.474
(gasps, sighs)

09:34.507 --> 09:37.077
Don't blame yourself
for this, baby.

09:37.110 --> 09:40.580
When I was lying
on the ground there,

09:40.614 --> 09:43.651
I thought for sure
I was gonna die,

09:43.684 --> 09:47.554
so I just...
started praying

09:47.587 --> 09:50.824
that God would save
the baby.

09:50.858 --> 09:52.592
(sniffles)

09:52.626 --> 09:56.630
And then moonlight came in
through the window, and I...

09:56.664 --> 09:59.266
I swear, I thought he answered.

09:59.299 --> 10:01.168
God saved you.

10:01.201 --> 10:03.436
No.

10:04.638 --> 10:07.074
No.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.843
Andre, no. Uh...

10:09.877 --> 10:11.211
God doesn't exist.

10:15.348 --> 10:16.784
Don't say that, Rhonda.

10:16.817 --> 10:20.187
If he did...

10:20.220 --> 10:23.423
then... the baby
would still be here.

10:23.456 --> 10:26.459
He didn't do anything
to anyone.

10:26.493 --> 10:27.961
(crying)

10:29.797 --> 10:32.132
There really is no God, Andre.

10:32.165 --> 10:34.735
(sobbing)

10:36.069 --> 10:38.471
(sobbing continues)

10:49.016 --> 10:51.018
Lucious?

10:54.988 --> 10:56.990
Lucious?

11:02.195 --> 11:04.597
Lucious?

11:07.534 --> 11:09.837
Hey.

11:09.870 --> 11:12.272
You okay?

11:28.455 --> 11:29.890
(sighs)

11:42.202 --> 11:45.205
(quiet clicking)

11:49.810 --> 11:52.379
(clicking)

11:54.748 --> 11:57.084
Lucious.

11:57.117 --> 11:58.852
The hell are you doing?

11:58.886 --> 12:01.288
I'm gonna take
my company back.

12:04.457 --> 12:08.095
I don't know how our son
turned out to be so rotten.

12:08.128 --> 12:09.662
(scoffs gently)

12:11.398 --> 12:14.968
Well, maybe the apple don't
fall too far from the tree.

12:19.606 --> 12:21.909
If he tries to
become CEO...

12:24.812 --> 12:27.614
...it ain't gonna
turn out good for him.

12:27.647 --> 12:29.449
Don't say that.

12:32.485 --> 12:33.887
I mean it, Cookie.

12:33.921 --> 12:35.422
Don't ever say that.

12:35.455 --> 12:37.657
I got another way in.

12:37.690 --> 12:40.760
I'm-a take Camilla out
from the inside.

12:40.794 --> 12:42.729
I just got to get
back into Empire.

12:42.762 --> 12:45.732
Yeah, how you
gonna get back in?

12:45.765 --> 12:48.101
You just let
Cookie handle that.

12:48.135 --> 12:49.837
Just give me two days

12:49.870 --> 12:52.072
before you go and do something
you gonna regret forever.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.640
(gun clicks)

12:53.673 --> 12:55.442
You got 48 hours.

12:56.676 --> 12:58.345
Bye.

12:58.378 --> 13:01.448
Put that damn thing away.

13:12.459 --> 13:13.827
Look at this, it's fabulous.

13:13.861 --> 13:15.362
This is our new clothing line.

13:15.395 --> 13:16.930
Yeah.

13:16.964 --> 13:18.665
I'm so sorry about
your brother's child.

13:18.698 --> 13:20.433
That was a tragedy.

13:20.467 --> 13:23.136
How long you been planning
to kick my dad off the throne?

13:25.138 --> 13:27.374
Since the day he banished me.

13:29.409 --> 13:31.344
Look, I've got
big plans for us.

13:31.378 --> 13:34.347
But you need to get rid of your
little Mexican girlfriend first.

13:34.381 --> 13:35.815
Babe, it's not that easy.

13:35.849 --> 13:37.484
I told you, I think
I'm in love with her.

13:37.517 --> 13:40.720
What would you say
if I made you CEO of Empire?

13:40.753 --> 13:44.124
Would you still be
in love with her then?

13:44.157 --> 13:46.526
You can make
that happen?

13:46.559 --> 13:48.395
I think so.

13:48.428 --> 13:51.798
The board wants Jago
Locke to take over,

13:51.831 --> 13:54.167
but if we can swing enough
votes, we can push you through.

13:54.201 --> 13:55.402
I know a vote you can get.

13:55.435 --> 13:57.404
Ma, what are you doing here?

13:57.437 --> 13:59.639
I'm here to make you
the deal of a lifetime, son.

13:59.672 --> 14:01.708
(chuckles)

14:01.741 --> 14:04.244
I'm gonna let you
acquire my company.

14:04.277 --> 14:06.846
And what's
in it for me?

14:06.880 --> 14:08.015
Hakeem Lyon,

14:08.048 --> 14:10.550
who as partner
of Lyon Dynasty

14:10.583 --> 14:11.985
is still under contract with us.

14:12.019 --> 14:13.453
He still belongs to me.

14:15.388 --> 14:17.224
How much?
20 million.

14:17.257 --> 14:19.159
(chuckles)
Never.

14:19.192 --> 14:21.028
Well, then you can't
have Hakeem, bitch.

14:21.061 --> 14:22.495
I already did.

14:22.529 --> 14:25.598
And I have no
problem suing you.

14:25.632 --> 14:28.235
I will crush you with
Empire legal bills.

14:28.268 --> 14:29.436
(chuckles)

14:29.469 --> 14:32.739
Hakeem, do you really
want to be CEO?

14:32.772 --> 14:35.275
Because I can make that
happen for you, baby,

14:35.308 --> 14:37.244
but I got to be here.

14:37.277 --> 14:38.946
See that scallywag next to you?

14:38.979 --> 14:41.181
She ain't got what it takes
to push out Jago out,

14:41.214 --> 14:42.950
but I can do it,
and you know it.

14:42.983 --> 14:46.419
This company is not gonna be
run like gangsters anymore.

14:46.453 --> 14:48.888
The answer is
no, Cookie.

14:55.462 --> 14:58.431
You really gonna pick this bitch
over your own family, Hakeem?

14:58.465 --> 15:00.800
At least she don't
beat me with a purse.

15:02.269 --> 15:04.671
Not unless you
want me to.

15:10.477 --> 15:11.478
(sniffs)

15:19.186 --> 15:21.254
(candy clattering)

15:21.288 --> 15:23.356
This is so childish.

15:26.793 --> 15:28.795
*

15:35.502 --> 15:37.337
Okay.

15:37.370 --> 15:39.139
Jago Locke.

15:39.172 --> 15:40.840
He's the leading
CEO contender,

15:40.873 --> 15:43.010
but after Guy has
a little talk with him,

15:43.043 --> 15:44.844
we expect him
to drop out.

